Dear Connection  INVITATION TO WORK AND FAMILY CONFERENCE, 2017  We are pleased to invite delegates from your company to the international conference, Work & Family 2017,  with the theme Work Family Integration: Employee Engagement Amidst Scarce Resources. What to do?   The conference is organized by the Institute for Work and Family Integration (IWFI) in collaboration with the Lagos Business School   taking place on Wednesday May 24th, 2017 Civic Center, Ozumba Mbadiwe road, Victoria Island, Lagos.   A select group of 200 decision makers including CEOs, senior executives and human resource directors and people managers  will come together to show how to keep employees sufficiently motivated in this current recession in Nigeria and the changing policies and cost saving measures. Anheuser-Busch InBev, West Africa Yves Mayilamene, Group Human Resource Head, Ecobank, Transnational Incorporated. Emmanuel Imaogene, Group Human Resources Director, Dangote Plc  I will be glad to send you the conference brochure on your request. To register delegates for this conference, log on to www.iwfionline.org/workandfamily2017.  I would be glad to answer any questions you might have as regards this conference, i can be reached on 08033867663, taiwo.olowokere@iwfionline.org. We look forward to welcoming delegates from your organization to this event.  Best regards,        Taiwo O. Davies Programmes & Advocacy Manager

RE: SPONSORSHIP IGNITE SCHOOL PROGRAM  We wish to present to your Bank an opportunity to join us in adding value to children by sponsoring our IGNITE SCHOOL PROGRAM a Personal Development and Life Skill Workshop for public schools.   IGNITE School Program is a child development program which provides ongoing personal Development tools helping student develop the skills of knowing self, decision making, problem solving, increase self-esteem and confidence, handling new situations, self-belief and increase in academic performance.  WHO WE ARE DINIAHS CONSULTING LIMITED is an Educational and Academic Performance Coaching Organisation working with schools to facilitate Change and to improve the character,and well-rounded education for ALL students. We are one of the pioneers of personal development for children and women in Nigeria.  Diniahs Consulting is of the opinion that school should be a place where children have a great number of opportunities to learn and the school environment is a place for holistic learners, we have worked with forward thinking school owners over the last three years and in June 2013 the Lagos State Education Board approved our workshop in public schools which led to our award in March 13th 2015, awarded by the Lagos State Government and Ministry of Education, for the Support our Schools Initiative â€œCorporate Social Responsibility Awardâ€.  OUR VISION With young children, there is the feeling of not being smart or good enough which can hold them back from stepping out and being the best thus an alarming number of children live with low self-esteem, misdirection, misinformation etc. but young people who are encouraged early to venture out of their comfort zones will have a happy life and a more successful future. This is what we want your company to join us achieve for every child.  Also, with our previous Girls Talk workshop, we have seen that a lot more girls need to be educated on puberty and proper hygiene during menstruation, even more surprising, some of these girls due to lack of money improvise with items like newspaper, handkerchief, cotton wool, tissue paper, rage, etc. resulting to infection or even hospitalization which they cannot afford, a lot of girls are also not aware of the use of deodorant.  OUR PROJECT I AM CLEAN CHAMPAIGN: providing Hygiene kit for girls and boys, and teaching on adolescents and puberty.  For the Girls Talk we have Champion  The mirror don't tell it all, every girl child is beautiful inside out, hygiene adolescent & puberty,Â  THINK CHAMPAIGN: Building self-confidence and esteem self-love also tools on making better decision. SPEAK CHAMPAIGN: Bullying, Sex Education, Sexual Abuse. A child's voice is her power, never think you are alone" EDUCATION CAMPAIGN: Importance of child education and back to school kit education is Empowerment, empower change, create hope and education should be for every child education is the futureÂ thus we are investing in the future of every child via our program   WHAT YOUR COMPANY STANDS TO GAIN We welcome you company and sponsorship to reach more children, impact more and to be able to continue with these course of child development.  In the last Three year we have reached out to over 50 schools and counting with more pupils/participants in the public schools, thus we will need more hands and more resource to continue these projects.  AS A MAJOR SPONSOR  Your company will receive the following Branding opportunity on all materials used on the workshop, roll up banner, t-shirt, files and writing materials, In every aspect of our workshop we promote both your company and its product An individual thank you on every IGNITE workshop as we will appreciate participation from your company so the children get to meet their sponsors. Recognition through all media opportunities,  We take your brand directly to the targeted consumers particularly on the Girls Talk workshop, creating favourable word of mouth feedback as the Girls Talk practical sessions cover most of your product and it is an opportunity to introduce new line of products your company has to offer â€œone on one advertâ€, and also create more opportunity for innovation Quarterly notes to keep update on all our activities; and Opportunity to help support the move of developing children and women positively, as we build confident leaders.  It is my firm believes, that this will be a partnership you and your organisation will value, and want to build upon, that we can work as a team, to building a great future for the young ones and our nation, investing in their potentials that will grow to change the system of our country Nigeria as young leaders who will not depend on the system of our country but rather will be the change that our country needs.  We will be honoured to partnering with your organisation to bring out the best in every child and we will appreciate your positive response. Kindly find attached a copy of the book and pictures of some of our workshop.  Best regards Yours faithfully  Barr. OLADIPUPO,    How are you? We are colleagues from Nigeria Human Resources | Recruitment | Job Connections! group, I was looking at your profile on Linkedin and I saw that you are Human Resource Officer and might be interested in a special invitation that we are doing for people like you. We would like to offer you a free trial for the PDA Psychometric Behavioral Assessment.    PDA is an online assessment that allows your people to improve leadership, communications and team building identifying their behavioral profile as well as assessing their compatibility with the positions and competencies required by the company.    Organizations such as Dupont, JPMorgan Chase, 3M, Roche, Accenture, McDonalds, Whirlpool, Pepsico, MasterCard, ADT, Nestle, Kimberly-Clark, Sheraton, Telecom, among other, and prestigious universities and business schools used PDA to improve their HR processes.    PDA rely on psychological investigations that support the results of the tests based on scales and personality traits and are supported by the standard reliability and validity coefficients required by the EEOC, the Labor Department and the Justice and Civil Service Commission.  You can access the PDA assessment for free just by registering your personal information at:      http://www.pdainternational.net/en/LIHRexclusive?id=315792805      Complete the PDA form then contact me and I will send you your Free personal PDA summary.    Please do not forward this message to other people because this is a special invitation for limited Linkedin members.      Regards, Andrew Rormoser  andrew.rormoser@pdainternational.net  +1 (888) 485-4385  http://www.pdainternational.net

CONVERSATION TITLE: UCL Institute for Global Prosperity â€“ MSc degrees in London
CONTENT:
Dear Femi O,


At the UCL Institute for Global Prosperity, we educate the problem solvers of the future. Our degrees give you new perspectives on global prosperity, allowing you to harness your entrepreneurial spirit and seek leadership positions to tackle today's major challenges.

 

UCL is located in central London and ranked amongst the worldâ€™s top 10 universities (QS). The Bartlett Faculty of the Built Environment is ranked as the #1 for Built Environment studies in the UK and #2 in the world.


We are currently accepting applications for two postgraduate programmes:


Our Global Prosperity MSc is an intensive one-year (or part-time) taught graduate degree. It challenges current economic and social models and explores how much-needed economic, social and political transformations can be enacted to deliver sustainable prosperity.


Our Prosperity, Innovation and Entrepreneurship MSc is an intensive one-year (or part-time) taught graduate degree. At the core of the programme is the concept of transformative entrepreneurship, which involves the development and implementation of innovations to address the causes and consequences of environmental degradation, economic inequality and social injustice.


Join a diverse community of researchers and practitioners underpinned by a shared vision for sustainable and inclusive prosperity. To learn more, please visit our site today or email igp@ucl.ac.uk.
